<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <h1>About This Project</h1>
    <hr>
    
    <h2>Data Sources</h2>
    <p>This music database application integrates data from multiple sources to provide comprehensive music information:</p>
    
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card mb-3">
          <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
            <h5>1. CSV File</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <p><strong>Source:</strong> Custom compiled CSV dataset</p>
            <p><strong>Data Type:</strong> Album and artist information</p>
            <p><strong>Contains:</strong> 50 classic and popular albums with release dates, popularity scores, and artist details</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card mb-3">
          <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
            <h5>2. Faker Gem (Artists)</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <p><strong>Source:</strong> Ruby Faker gem</p>
            <p><strong>Data Type:</strong> Additional artist profiles</p>
            <p><strong>Contains:</strong> Generated artist biographies, countries, and formation years</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card mb-3">
          <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
            <h5>3. Faker Gem (Reviews)</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <p><strong>Source:</strong> Ruby Faker gem</p>
            <p><strong>Data Type:</strong> User reviews and ratings</p>
            <p><strong>Contains:</strong> <%= Review.count %> reviews with ratings (1-5 stars), reviewer names, and comments</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2 class="mt-4">Database Structure</h2>
    <p>The database consists of <%= Artist.count %> artists, <%= Album.count %> albums, <%= Genre.count %> genres, and <%= Review.count %> reviews.</p>
    
    <h3>Relationships</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>One-to-Many:</strong> Artists → Albums (each artist can have multiple albums)</li>
      <li><strong>One-to-Many:</strong> Albums → Reviews (each album can have multiple reviews)</li>
      <li><strong>Many-to-Many:</strong> Albums ↔ Genres (albums can belong to multiple genres)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 class="mt-4">Features</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Browse all albums with pagination</li>
      <li>Search albums by title or artist name</li>
      <li>Filter albums by genre (hierarchical search)</li>
      <li>View detailed album information including reviews</li>
      <li>Explore artists and their discographies</li>
      <li>Navigate genres and discover related albums</li>
      <li>Responsive Bootstrap-based design</li>
      <li>Valid HTML5 markup</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 class="mt-4">Database Statistics</h2>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <div class="alert alert-primary">
          <h4><%= Artist.count %></h4>
          <p>Artists</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <div class="alert alert-success">
          <h4><%= Album.count %></h4>
          <p>Albums</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <div class="alert alert-info">
          <h4><%= Genre.count %></h4>
          <p>Genres</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
        <div class="alert alert-warning">
          <h4><%= Review.count %></h4>
          <p>Reviews</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <%= link_to "Back to Home", root_path, class: "btn btn-primary mt-3" %>
  </div>
</div>
